obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (5290)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5290&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Integrated Goods and`
  line `Services Tax Act, 2017.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall extend to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any reference`
  line `in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming`
  line `into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the state of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 27 of 2017, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-7-2017).`
  line
  line `2. 22nd June, 2017 for sections 1, 2, 3, 14, 20 and 22 vide notification No. G.S.R. 603 (E) dated the 19th June, 2017, see Gazette`
  line `of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
  line
  line `1st July, 2017 for sections 4 to 13, 16 to 19, 21, 23 to 25 vide notification No. G.S.R. 662(E) dated 28th June`
  line `2017, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (5291)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5291&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(1) "Central Goods and Services Tax Act" means the Central Goods and Services Tax Act, 2017;`
  line
  line `(2) "central tax" means the tax levied and collected under the Central Goods and Services Tax`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(3) "continuous journey" means a journey for which a single or more than one ticket or invoice is issued at the same time, either by a single supplier of service or through an agent acting on behalf of`
  line `more than one supplier of service, and which involves no stopover between any of the legs of the`
  line `journey for which one or more separate tickets or invoices are issued.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this clause, the term "stopover" means a place where a`
  line `passenger can disembark either to transfer to another conveyance or break his journey for a certain`
  line `period in order to resume it at a later point of time;`
  line
  line `(4) "customs frontiers of India" means the limits of a customs area as defined in section 2 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962);`
  line
  line `(5) "export of goods" with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means taking`
  line `goods out of India to a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(6) "export of services" means the supply of any service when,---`
  line
  line `(i) the supplier of service is located in India;`
  line
  line `(ii) the recipient of service is located outside India;`
  line
  line `(iii) the place of supply of service is outside India;`
  line
  line `(iv) the payment for such service has been received by the supplier of service in convertible`
  line `foreign exchange; ^1[or in Indian rupees wherever permitted by the Reserve Bank of India]; and`
  line
  line `(v) the supplier of service and the recipient of service are not merely establishments of a`
  line `distinct person in accordance with Explanation 1 in section 8;`
  line
  line `(7) "fixed establishment" means a place (other than the registered place of business) which is`
  line `characterised by a sufficient degree of permanence and suitable structure in terms of human and`
  line `technical resources to supply services or to receive and use services for its own needs;`
  line
  line `(8) "Goods and Services Tax (Compensation to States) Act" means the Goods and Services Tax`
  line `(Compensation to States) Act, 2017;`
  line
  line `(9) "Government" means the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(10) "import of goods" with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means bringing goods into India from a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(11) "import of services" means the supply of any service, where---`
  line
  line `(i) the supplier of service is located outside India;`
  line
  line `(ii) the recipient of service is located in India; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the place of supply of service is in India;`
  line
  line `(12) "integrated tax" means the integrated goods and services tax levied under this Act;`
  line
  line `(13) "intermediary" means a broker, an agent or any other person, by whatever name called, who arranges or facilitates the supply of goods or services or both, or securities, between two or more`
  line `persons, but does not include a person who supplies such goods or services or both or securities on his`
  line `own account;`
  line
  line `(14) "location of the recipient of services" means,---`
  line
  line `(a) where a supply is received at a place of business for which the registration has been`
  line `obtained, the location of such place of business;`
  line
  line `(b) where a supply is received at a place other than the place of business for which`
  line `registration has been obtained (a fixed establishment elsewhere), the location of such fixed`
  line establishment;
  line
  line `(c) where a supply is received at more than one establishment, whether the place of business`
  line `or fixed establishment, the location of the establishment most directly concerned with the receipt`
  line `of the supply; and`
  line
  line `(d) in absence of such places, the location of the usual place of residence of the recipient;`
  line
  line `(15) "location of the supplier of services" means,---`
  line
  line `(a) where a supply is made from a place of business for which the registration has been`
  line `obtained, the location of such place of business;`
  line
  line `(b) where a supply is made from a place other than the place of business for which`
  line `registration has been obtained (a fixed establishment elsewhere), the location of such fixed`
  line establishment;
  line
  line `(c) where a supply is made from more than one establishment, whether the place of business`
  line `or fixed establishment, the location of the establishment most directly concerned with the`
  line `provision of the supply; and`
  line
  line `(d) in absence of such places, the location of the usual place of residence of the supplier;`
  line
  line `^2[(16) "non-taxable online recipient" means any unregistered person receiving online information and database access or retrieval services located in taxable territory.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this clause, the expression "unregistered person" includes a person registered solely in terms of clause (vi) of section 24 of the Central Goods and Services Tax Act, 2017 (12 of 2017); ]`
  line
  line `(17) "online information and database access or retrieval services" means services whose delivery is mediated by information technology over the internet or an electronic network and the nature of which renders their supply ^3 *** impossible to ensure in the absence of information technology and includes electronic services such`
  line as,---
  line
  line `(i) advertising on the internet;`
  line
  line `(ii) providing cloud services;`
  line
  line `(iii) provision of e-books, movie, music, software and other intangibles through`
  line `telecommunication networks or internet;`
  line
  line `(iv) providing data or information, retrievable or otherwise, to any person in electronic form`
  line `through a computer network;`
  line
  line `(v) online supplies of digital content (movies, television shows, music and the like);`
  line
  line `(vi) digital data storage; and`
  line
  line `^4[(vii) online gaming, excluding the online money gaming as defined in clause (80B) of section 2 of the Central Goods and Services Tax Act, 2017 (12 of 2017); ]`
  line
  line `(18) "output tax", in relation to a taxable person, means the integrated tax chargeable under this`
  line `Act on taxable supply of goods or services or both made by him or by his agent but excludes tax`
  line `payable by him on reverse charge basis;`
  line
  line `(19) "Special Economic Zone" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (za) of`
  line `section 2 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005);`
  line
  line `(20) "Special Economic Zone developer" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in`
  line `clause (g) of section 2 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005) and includes an`
  line `Authority as defined in clause (d) and a Co-Developer as defined in clause (f) of section 2 of the said`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(21) "supply" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 7 of the Central Goods and`
  line `Services Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(22) "taxable territory" means the territory to which the provisions of this Act apply;`
  line
  line `(23) "zero-rated supply" shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 16;`
  line
  line `(24) words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Central Goods and`
  line `Services Tax Act, the Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act and the Goods and Services Tax`
  line `(Compensation to States) Act shall have the same meaning as assigned to them in those Acts;`
  line
  line `(25) any reference in this Act to a law which is not in force in the State of Jammu and Kashmir*,`
  line `shall, in relation to that State be construed as a reference to the corresponding law, if any, in force in`
  line `that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2018, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 160, for clause (16) (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Certain words omitted by Act 8 of 2023, s. 160 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 31 of 2023, s. 2, for sub-clause (vii) (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (5292)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Appointment of officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5292&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Board may appoint such central tax officers as it thinks fit for`
  line `exercising the powers under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (5293)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Authorisation of officers of State tax or Union territory tax as proper officer in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5293&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions of this Act, the officers appointed under the State`
  line `Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act are authorised to be the`
  line `proper officers for the purposes of this Act, subject to such exceptions and conditions as the Government`
  line `shall, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (5294)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Levy and collection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5294&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), there shall be levied a tax`
  line `called the integrated goods and services tax on all inter-State supplies of goods or services or both, except on the supply of alcoholic liquor for human consumption ^1[and un-denatured extra neutral alcohol or`
  line `rectified spirit used for manufacture of alcoholic liquor, for human consumption], on the value determined under section 15 of the`
  line `Central Goods and Services Tax Act and at such rates, not exceeding forty per cent., as may be notified by`
  line `the Government on the recommendations of the Council and collected in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed and shall be paid by the taxable person:`
  line
  line `Provided that the integrated tax on goods ^2[other than the goods as may be notified by the Government on the recommendations of the Council] imported into India shall be levied and collected in accordance with the provisions of section 3 of the Customs Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975) on the value as determined under the said Act at the point when duties of customs are levied on the said goods under section 12 of the Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962).`
  line
  line `(2) The integrated tax on the supply of petroleum crude, high speed diesel, motor spirit (commonly`
  line `known as petrol), natural gas and aviation turbine fuel shall be levied with effect from such date as may be notified by the Government on the recommendations of the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, specify categories`
  line `of supply of goods or services or both, the tax on which shall be paid on reverse charge basis by the`
  line `recipient of such goods or services or both and all the provisions of this Act shall apply to such recipient`
  line `as if he is the person liable for paying the tax in relation to the supply of such goods or services or both.`
  line
  line `^3[(4) The Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, specify a class of registered persons who shall, in respect of supply of specified categories of goods or services or both received from an unregistered supplier, pay the tax on reverse charge basis as the recipient of such supply of goods or services or both, and all the provisions of this Act shall apply to such recipient as if he is the`
  line `person liable for paying the tax in relation to such supply of goods or services or both.]`
  line
  line `(5) The Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, specify categories`
  line `of services, the tax on inter-State supplies of which shall be paid by the electronic commerce operator if`
  line `such services are supplied through it, and all the provisions of this Act shall apply to such electronic`
  line `commerce operator as if he is the supplier liable for paying the tax in relation to the supply of such`
  line `services:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an electronic commerce operator does not have a physical presence in the taxable`
  line `territory, any person representing such electronic commerce operator for any purpose in the taxable`
  line `territory shall be liable to pay tax:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where an electronic commerce operator does not have a physical presence in the`
  line `taxable territory and also does not have a representative in the said territory, such electronic commerce`
  line `operator shall appoint a person in the taxable territory for the purpose of paying tax and such person shall`
  line `be liable to pay tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 151 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 31 of 2023, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 2018, s. 3, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (5295)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to grant exemption from tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5295&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Government is satisfied that it is necessary`
  line `in the public interest so to do, it may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, exempt`
  line `generally, either absolutely or subject to such conditions as may be specified therein, goods or services or`
  line `both of any specified description from the whole or any part of the tax leviable thereon with effect from`
  line `such date as may be specified in such notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Government is satisfied that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, it may, on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council, by special order in each case, under circumstances of an exceptional`
  line `nature to be stated in such order, exempt from payment of tax any goods or services or both on which tax`
  line `is leviable.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government may, if it considers necessary or expedient so to do for the purpose of clarifying`
  line `the scope or applicability of any notification issued under sub-section (1) or order issued under`
  line `sub-section (2), insert an Explanation in such notification or order, as the case may be, by notification at`
  line `any time within one year of issue of the notification under sub-section (1) or order under sub-section (2),`
  line `and every such Explanation shall have effect as if it had always been the part of the first such notification`
  line `or order, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, where an exemption in respect of any goods or`
  line `services or both from the whole or part of the tax leviable thereon has been granted absolutely, the`
  line `registered person supplying such goods or services or both shall not collect the tax, in excess of the`
  line `effective rate, on such supply of goods or services or both.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (98254)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 7
  title `Power not to recover Goods and Services Tax not levied or short-levied as a result of general practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 152 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=98254&sectionno=6A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Power not to recover Goods and Services Tax not levied or short-levied as a result of`
  line `general practice.--- Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if the Government is satisfied that---`
  line
  line `(a) a practice was, or is, generally prevalent regarding levy of integrated tax (including non-levy`
  line `thereof) on any supply of goods or services or both; and`
  line
  line `(b) such supplies were, or are, liable to---`
  line
  line `(i) integrated tax, in cases where according to the said practice, integrated tax was not, or is`
  line `not being, levied; or`
  line
  line `(ii) a higher amount of integrated tax than what was, or is being, levied, in accordance with`
  line `the said practice,`
  line
  line `the Government may, on the recommendation of the Council, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct`
  line `that the whole of the integrated tax payable on such supplies, or, as the case may be, the integrated tax in`
  line `excess of that payable on such supplies, but for the said practice, shall not be required to be paid in respect`
  line `of the supplies on which the integrated tax was not, or is not being, levied, or was, or is being,`
  line `short-levied, in accordance with the said practice.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (5296)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Inter-State supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5296&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 10, supply of goods, where the`
  line `location of the supplier and the place of supply are in---`
  line
  line `(a) two different States;`
  line
  line `(b) two different Union territories; or`
  line
  line `(c) a State and a Union territory,`
  line
  line `shall be treated as a supply of goods in the course of inter-State trade or commerce.`
  line
  line `(2) Supply of goods imported into the territory of India, till they cross the customs frontiers of India,`
  line `shall be treated to be a supply of goods in the course of inter-State trade or commerce.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of section 12, supply of services, where the location of the supplier and`
  line `the place of supply are in---`
  line
  line `(a) two different States; or`
  line
  line `(b) two different Union territories; or`
  line
  line `(c) a State and a Union territory,`
  line
  line `shall be treated as a supply of services in the course of inter-State trade or commerce.`
  line
  line `(4) Supply of services imported into the territory of India shall be treated to be a supply of services in`
  line `the course of inter-State trade or commerce.`
  line
  line `(5) Supply of goods or services or both,---`
  line
  line `(a) when the supplier is located in India and the place of supply is outside India;`
  line
  line `(b) to or by a Special Economic Zone developer or a Special Economic Zone unit; or`
  line
  line `(c) in the taxable territory, not being an intra-State supply and not covered elsewhere in this`
  line section,
  line
  line `shall be treated to be a supply of goods or services or both in the course of inter-State trade or commerce.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (5297)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Intra-State supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. The words "being a business vertical" omitted by Act 32 of 2018, s. 4 (w.e.f 1-2-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5297&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 10, supply of goods where the`
  line `location of the supplier and the place of supply of goods are in the same State or same Union territory`
  line `shall be treated as intra-State supply:`
  line
  line `Provided that the following supply of goods shall not be treated as intra-State supply, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) supply of goods to or by a Special Economic Zone developer or a Special Economic Zone unit;`
  line
  line `(ii) goods imported into the territory of India till they cross the customs frontiers of India; or`
  line
  line `(iii) supplies made to a tourist referred to in section 15.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of section 12, supply of services where the location of the supplier and`
  line `the place of supply of services are in the same State or same Union territory shall be treated as intra-State`
  line `supply:`
  line
  line `Provided that the intra-State supply of services shall not include supply of services to or by a Special`
  line `Economic Zone developer or a Special Economic Zone unit.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.---For the purposes of this Act, where a person has,---`
  line
  line `(i) an establishment in India and any other establishment outside India;`
  line
  line `(ii) an establishment in a State or Union territory and any other establishment outside that State or`
  line `Union territory; or`
  line
  line `(iii) an establishment in a State or Union territory and any other establishment ^1*** registered within that State or Union territory,`
  line
  line `then such establishments shall be treated as establishments of distinct persons.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--- A person carrying on a business through a branch or an agency or a representational`
  line `office in any territory shall be treated as having an establishment in that territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (5298)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Supplies in territorial waters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5298&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,---`
  line
  line `(a) where the location of the supplier is in the territorial waters, the location of such supplier; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the place of supply is in the territorial waters, the place of supply,`
  line
  line `shall, for the purposes of this Act, be deemed to be in the coastal State or Union territory where the`
  line `nearest point of the appropriate baseline is located.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (5299)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Place of supply of goods other than supply of goods imported into, or exported from India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2023, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5299&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The place of supply of goods, other than supply of goods imported into, or exported from India, shall`
  line `be as under,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the supply involves movement of goods, whether by the supplier or the recipient or by`
  line `any other person, the place of supply of such goods shall be the location of the goods at the time at`
  line `which the movement of goods terminates for delivery to the recipient;`
  line
  line `(b) where the goods are delivered by the supplier to a recipient or any other person on the`
  line `direction of a third person, whether acting as an agent or otherwise, before or during movement of`
  line `goods, either by way of transfer of documents of title to the goods or otherwise, it shall be deemed`
  line `that the said third person has received the goods and the place of supply of such goods shall be the`
  line `principal place of business of such person;`
  line
  line `(c) where the supply does not involve movement of goods, whether by the supplier or the`
  line `recipient, the place of supply shall be the location of such goods at the time of the delivery to the`
  line recipient;
  line
  line `^1[(ca) where the supply of goods is made to a person other than a registered person, the place of`
  line `supply shall, notwithstanding anything contrary contained in clause (a) or clause (c), be the location`
  line `as per the address of the said person recorded in the invoice issued in respect of the said supply and`
  line `the location of the supplier where the address of the said person is not recorded in the invoice.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, recording of the name of the State of the said`
  line `person in the invoice shall be deemed to be the recording of the address of the said person;]`
  line
  line `(d) where the goods are assembled or installed at site, the place of supply shall be the place of`
  line `such installation or assembly;`
  line
  line `(e) where the goods are supplied on board a conveyance, including a vessel, an aircraft, a train or`
  line `a motor vehicle, the place of supply shall be the location at which such goods are taken on board.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the place of supply of goods cannot be determined, the place of supply shall be determined`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (5300)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Place of supply of goods imported into, or exported from India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5300&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The place of supply of`
  line goods,--
  line
  line `(a) imported into India shall be the location of the importer;`
  line
  line `(b) exported from India shall be the location outside India.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (5301)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Place of supply of services where location of supplier and recipient is in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. omitted by Act 8 of 2023, s. 161 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5301&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `provisions of this section shall apply to determine the place of supply of services where the location of`
  line `supplier of services and the location of the recipient of services is in India.`
  line
  line `(2) The place of supply of services, except the services specified in sub-sections (3) to (14),--`
  line
  line `(a) made to a registered person shall be the location of such person;`
  line
  line `(b) made to any person other than a registered person shall be,`
  line
  line `(i) the location of the recipient where the address on record exists; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the location of the supplier of services in other cases.`
  line
  line `(3) The place of supply of services,---`
  line
  line `(a) directly in relation to an immovable property, including services provided by architects,`
  line `interior decorators, surveyors, engineers and other related experts or estate agents, any service`
  line `provided by way of grant of rights to use immovable property or for carrying out or co-ordination of`
  line `construction work; or`
  line
  line `(b) by way of lodging accommodation by a hotel, inn, guest house, home stay, club or campsite,`
  line `by whatever name called, and including a house boat or any other vessel; or`
  line
  line `(c) by way of accommodation in any immovable property for organising any marriage or`
  line `reception or matters related thereto, official, social, cultural, religious or business function including`
  line `services provided in relation to such function at such property; or`
  line
  line `(d) any services ancillary to the services referred to in clauses (a), (b) and (c),`
  line
  line `shall be the location at which the immovable property or boat or vessel, as the case may be, is located or`
  line `intended to be located:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the location of the immovable property or boat or vessel is located or intended to be`
  line `located outside India, the place of supply shall be the location of the recipient.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---Where the immovable property or boat or vessel is located in more than one State or`
  line `Union territory, the supply of services shall be treated as made in each of the respective States or Union territories, in proportion to the value for services separately collected or determined in terms of the contract or agreement entered into in this regard or, in the absence of such contract or agreement, on such other basis as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The place of supply of restaurant and catering services, personal grooming, fitness, beauty`
  line `treatment, health service including cosmetic and plastic surgery shall be the location where the services`
  line `are actually performed.`
  line
  line `(5) The place of supply of services in relation to training and performance appraisal to,---`
  line
  line `(a) a registered person, shall be the location of such person;`
  line
  line `(b) a person other than a registered person, shall be the location where the services are actually`
  line performed.
  line
  line `(6) The place of supply of services provided by way of admission to a cultural, artistic, sporting,`
  line `scientific, educational, entertainment event or amusement park or any other place and services ancillary`
  line `thereto, shall be the place where the event is actually held or where the park or such other place is located.`
  line
  line `(7) The place of supply of services provided by way of,---`
  line
  line `(a) organisation of a cultural, artistic, sporting, scientific, educational or entertainment event`
  line `including supply of services in relation to a conference, fair, exhibition, celebration or similar events;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) services ancillary to organisation of any of the events or services referred to in clause (a), or`
  line `assigning of sponsorship to such events,---`
  line
  line `(i) to a registered person, shall be the location of such person;`
  line
  line `(ii) to a person other than a registered person, shall be the place where the event is actually`
  line `held and if the event is held outside India, the place of supply shall be the location of the`
  line recipient.
  line
  line `Explanation.---Where the event is held in more than one State or Union territory and a`
  line `consolidated amount is charged for supply of services relating to such event, the place of supply of`
  line `such services shall be taken as being in each of the respective States or Union territories in proportion`
  line `to the value for services separately collected or determined in terms of the contract or agreement`
  line `entered into in this regard or, in the absence of such contract or agreement, on such other basis as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) The place of supply of services by way of transportation of goods, including by mail or courier`
  line `to, ---`
  line
  line `(a) a registered person, shall be the location of such person;`
  line
  line `(b) a person other than a registered person, shall be the location at which such goods are handed over for their transportation.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(9) The place of supply of passenger transportation service to, ---`
  line
  line `(a) a registered person, shall be the location of such person;`
  line
  line `(b) a person other than a registered person, shall be the place where the passenger embarks on the`
  line `conveyance for a continuous journey:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the right to passage is given for future use and the point of embarkation is not`
  line `known at the time of issue of right to passage, the place of supply of such service shall be determined`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section, the return journey shall be treated as a`
  line `separate journey, even if the right to passage for onward and return journey is issued at the same time.`
  line
  line `(10) The place of supply of services on board a conveyance, including a vessel, an aircraft, a train or a`
  line `motor vehicle, shall be the location of the first scheduled point of departure of that conveyance for the`
  line journey.
  line
  line `(11) The place of supply of telecommunication services including data transfer, broadcasting, cable`
  line `and direct to home television services to any person shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) in case of services by way of fixed telecommunication line, leased circuits, internet leased`
  line `circuit, cable or dish antenna, be the location where the telecommunication line, leased circuit or cable`
  line `connection or dish antenna is installed for receipt of services;`
  line
  line `(b) in case of mobile connection for telecommunication and internet services provided on`
  line `post-paid basis, be the location of billing address of the recipient of services on the record of the`
  line `supplier of services;`
  line
  line `(c) in cases where mobile connection for telecommunication, internet service and direct to home`
  line `television services are provided on pre-payment basis through a voucher or any other means,---`
  line
  line `(i) through a selling agent or a re-seller or a distributor of subscriber identity module card or`
  line `re-charge voucher, be the address of the selling agent or re-seller or distributor as per the record of`
  line `the supplier at the time of supply; or`
  line
  line `(ii) by any person to the final subscriber, be the location where such prepayment is received`
  line `or such vouchers are sold;`
  line
  line `(d) in other cases, be the address of the recipient as per the records of the supplier of services and`
  line `where such address is not available, the place of supply shall be location of the supplier of services:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the address of the recipient as per the records of the supplier of services is not`
  line `available, the place of supply shall be location of the supplier of services:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if such pre-paid service is availed or the recharge is made through internet`
  line `banking or other electronic mode of payment, the location of the recipient of services on the record of`
  line `the supplier of services shall be the place of supply of such services.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where the leased circuit is installed in more than one State or Union territory and a`
  line `consolidated amount is charged for supply of services relating to such circuit, the place of supply of such`
  line `services shall be taken as being in each of the respective States or Union territories in proportion to the`
  line `value for services separately collected or determined in terms of the contract or agreement entered into in`
  line `this regard or, in the absence of such contract or agreement, on such other basis as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(12) The place of supply of banking and other financial services, including stock broking services to`
  line `any person shall be the location of the recipient of services on the records of the supplier of services:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the location of recipient of services is not on the records of the supplier, the place of`
  line `supply shall be the location of the supplier of services.`
  line
  line `(13) The place of supply of insurance services shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) to a registered person, be the location of such person;`
  line
  line `(b) to a person other than a registered person, be the location of the recipient of services on the`
  line `records of the supplier of services.`
  line
  line `(14) The place of supply of advertisement services to the Central Government, a State Government, a`
  line `statutory body or a local authority meant for the States or Union territories identified in the contract or`
  line `agreement shall be taken as being in each of such States or Union territories and the value of such supplies`
  line `specific to each State or Union territory shall be in proportion to the amount attributable to services`
  line `provided by way of dissemination in the respective States or Union territories as may be determined in`
  line `terms of the contract or agreement entered into in this regard or, in the absence of such contract or`
  line `agreement, on such other basis as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (5302)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Place of supply of services where location of supplier or location of recipient is outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5302&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this section shall apply to determine the place of supply of services where`
  line `the location of the supplier of services or the location of the recipient of services is outside India.`
  line
  line `(2) The place of supply of services except the services specified in sub-sections (3) to (13) shall be the`
  line `location of the recipient of services:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the location of the recipient of services is not available in the ordinary course of`
  line `business, the place of supply shall be the location of the supplier of services.`
  line
  line `(3) The place of supply of the following services shall be the location where the services are actually`
  line `performed, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) services supplied in respect of goods which are required to be made physically available by`
  line `the recipient of services to the supplier of services, or to a person acting on behalf of the supplier of`
  line `services in order to provide the services:`
  line
  line `Provided that when such services are provided from a remote location by way of electronic`
  line `means, the place of supply shall be the location where goods are situated at the time of supply of`
  line `services:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that nothing contained in this clause shall apply in the case of services supplied in respect of goods which are temporarily imported into India for repairs or for any other treatment or process and are exported after such repairs or treatment or process without being put to any use in India, other than that which is required for such repairs or treatment or process;]`
  line
  line `(b) services supplied to an individual, represented either as the recipient of services or a person`
  line `acting on behalf of the recipient, which require the physical presence of the recipient or the person`
  line `acting on his behalf, with the supplier for the supply of services.`
  line
  line `(4) The place of supply of services supplied directly in relation to an immovable property, including`
  line `services supplied in this regard by experts and estate agents, supply of accommodation by a hotel, inn,`
  line `guest house, club or campsite, by whatever name called, grant of rights to use immovable property,`
  line `services for carrying out or co-ordination of construction work, including that of architects or interior`
  line `decorators, shall be the place where the immovable property is located or intended to be located.`
  line
  line `(5) The place of supply of services supplied by way of admission to, or organisation of a cultural,`
  line `artistic, sporting, scientific, educational or entertainment event, or a celebration, conference, fair,`
  line `exhibition or similar events, and of services ancillary to such admission or organisation, shall be the place`
  line `where the event is actually held.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any services referred to in sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) is supplied`
  line `at more than one location, including a location in the taxable territory, its place of supply shall be the`
  line `location in the taxable territory.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the services referred to in sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) are supplied`
  line `in more than one State or Union territory, the place of supply of such services shall be taken as being in`
  line `each of the respective States or Union territories and the value of such supplies specific to each State or`
  line `Union territory shall be in proportion to the value for services separately collected or determined in terms`
  line `of the contract or agreement entered into in this regard or, in the absence of such contract or agreement,`
  line `on such other basis as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) The place of supply of the following services shall be the location of the supplier of services,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) services supplied by a banking company, or a financial institution, or a non-banking financial`
  line `company, to account holders;`
  line
  line `(b) intermediary services;`
  line
  line `(c) services consisting of hiring of means of transport, including yachts but excluding aircrafts`
  line `and vessels, up to a period of one month.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression,---`
  line
  line `(a) "account" means an account bearing interest to the depositor, and includes a non-resident`
  line `external account and a non-resident ordinary account;`
  line
  line `(b) "banking company" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it under clause (a) of`
  line `section 45A of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(c) "financial institution" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (c) of`
  line `section 45-I of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(d) "non-banking financial company" means,---`
  line
  line `(i) a financial institution which is a company;`
  line
  line `(ii) a non-banking institution which is a company and which has as its principal business`
  line `the receiving of deposits, under any scheme or arrangement or in any other manner, or`
  line `lending in any manner; or`
  line
  line `(iii) such other non-banking institution or class of such institutions, as the Reserve Bank`
  line `of India may, with the previous approval of the Central Government and by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(10) The place of supply in respect of passenger transportation services shall be the place where the`
  line `passenger embarks on the conveyance for a continuous journey.`
  line
  line `(11) The place of supply of services provided on board a conveyance during the course of a passenger`
  line `transport operation, including services intended to be wholly or substantially consumed while on board,`
  line `shall be the first scheduled point of departure of that conveyance for the journey.`
  line
  line `(12) The place of supply of online information and database access or retrieval services shall be the`
  line `location of the recipient of services.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, person receiving such services shall be deemed to be located in the taxable territory, if any two of the following non-contradictory conditions are satisfied,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the location of address presented by the recipient of services through internet is in the taxable`
  line territory;
  line
  line `(b) the credit card or debit card or store value card or charge card or smart card or any other card`
  line `by which the recipient of services settles payment has been issued in the taxable territory;`
  line
  line `(c) the billing address of the recipient of services is in the taxable territory;`
  line
  line `(d) the internet protocol address of the device used by the recipient of services is in the taxable`
  line territory;
  line
  line `(e) the bank of the recipient of services in which the account used for payment is maintained is in`
  line `the taxable territory;`
  line
  line `(f) the country code of the subscriber identity module card used by the recipient of services is of taxable territory;`
  line
  line `(g) the location of the fixed land line through which the service is received by the recipient is in the taxable territory.`
  line
  line `(13) In order to prevent double taxation or non-taxation of the supply of a service, or for the uniform application of rules, the Government shall have the power to notify any description of services or circumstances in which the place of supply shall be the place of effective use and enjoyment of a service.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 2018, s. 6 for the second proviso (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (9) omitted by Act 8 of 2023, s. 162 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (5303)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Special provision for payment of tax by a supplier of online information and database access or retrieval services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5303&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) On supply of online information and database access or retrieval services by`
  line `any person located in a non-taxable territory and received by a non-taxable online recipient, the supplier`
  line `of services located in a non-taxable territory shall be the person liable for paying integrated tax on such`
  line `supply of services:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of supply of online information and database access or retrieval services by`
  line `any person located in a non-taxable territory and received by a non-taxable online recipient, an`
  line `intermediary located in the non-taxable territory, who arranges or facilitates the supply of such services,`
  line `shall be deemed to be the recipient of such services from the supplier of services in non-taxable territory`
  line `and supplying such services to the non-taxable online recipient except when such intermediary satisfies`
  line `the following conditions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the invoice or customers bill or receipt issued or made available by such intermediary taking`
  line `part in the supply clearly identifies the service in question and its supplier in non-taxable territory;`
  line
  line `(b) the intermediary involved in the supply does not authorise the charge to the customer or take`
  line `part in its charge which is that the intermediary neither collects or processes payment in any manner`
  line `nor is responsible for the payment between the non-taxable online recipient and the supplier of such`
  line services;
  line
  line `(c) the intermediary involved in the supply does not authorise delivery; and`
  line
  line `(d) the general terms and conditions of the supply are not set by the intermediary involved in the`
  line `supply but by the supplier of services.`
  line
  line `(2) The supplier of online information and database access or retrieval services referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) shall, for payment of integrated tax, take a single registration under the Simplified`
  line `Registration Scheme to be notified by the Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person located in the taxable territory representing such supplier for any purpose in`
  line `the taxable territory shall get registered and pay integrated tax on behalf of the supplier:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if such supplier does not have a physical presence or does not have a`
  line `representative for any purpose in the taxable territory, he may appoint a person in the taxable territory for`
  line `the purpose of paying integrated tax and such person shall be liable for payment of such tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (92418)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 16
  title `Special provision for specified actionable claims supplied by a person located outside taxable territory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2023, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=92418&sectionno=14A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[14A. Special provision for specified actionable claims supplied by a person located outside`
  line `taxable territory. —(1) A supplier of online money gaming as defined in clause (80B) of section 2 of the`
  line `Central Goods and Services Tax Act, 2017 (12 of 2017), not located in the taxable territory, shall in`
  line `respect of the supply of online money gaming by him to a person in the taxable territory, be liable to pay`
  line `integrated tax on such supply.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of complying with provisions of sub-section (1), the supplier of online money`
  line `gaming shall obtain a single registration under the Simplified Registration Scheme referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 14 of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person located in the taxable territory representing such supplier for any purpose in`
  line `the taxable territory shall get registered and pay the integrated tax on behalf of the supplier:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if such supplier does not have a physical presence or does not have a`
  line `representative for any purpose in the taxable territory, he shall appoint a person in the taxable territory for`
  line `the purpose of paying integrated tax and such person shall be liable for payment of such tax.`
  line
  line `(3) In case of failure to comply with provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) by the supplier of`
  line `the online money gaming or a person appointed by such supplier or both, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 69A of the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000), any information`
  line `generated, transmitted, received or hosted in any computer resource used for supply of online money`
  line `gaming by such supplier shall be liable to be blocked for access by the public in such manner as specified`
  line `in the said Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (5304)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Refund of integrated tax paid on supply of goods to tourist leaving India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5304&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The integrated tax`
  line `paid by tourist leaving India on any supply of goods taken out of India by him shall be refunded in such`
  line `manner and subject to such conditions and safeguards as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the term "tourist" means a person not normally`
  line `resident in India, who enters India for a stay of not more than six months for legitimate non-immigrant`
  line purposes.
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (5305)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Zero rated supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5305&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) "zero rated supply" means any of the following supplies of goods or`
  line `services or both, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) export of goods or services or both; or`
  line
  line `(b) supply of goods or services or both ^1[for authorised operations] to a Special Economic Zone developer or a Special`
  line `Economic Zone unit.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (5) of section 17 of the Central Goods and Services Tax`
  line `Act, credit of input tax may be availed for making zero-rated supplies, notwithstanding that such supply`
  line `may be an exempt supply.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) A registered person making zero rated supply shall be eligible to claim refund of unutilised input`
  line `tax credit on supply of goods or services or both, without payment of integrated tax, under bond or Letter`
  line `of Undertaking, in accordance with the provisions of section 54 of the Central Goods and Services Tax`
  line `Act or the rules made thereunder, subject to such conditions, safeguards and procedure as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the registered person making zero rated supply of goods shall, in case of non-realisation`
  line `of sale proceeds, be liable to deposit the refund so received under this sub-section along with the`
  line `applicable interest under section 50 of the Central Goods and Services Tax Act within thirty days after the`
  line `expiry of the time limit prescribed under the Foreign Exchange Management Act, 1999 (42 of 1999) for`
  line `receipt of foreign exchange remittances, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Government may, on the recommendation of the Council, and subject to such conditions,`
  line `safeguards and procedures, by notification, specify---`
  line
  line `(i) a class of persons who may make zero rated supply on payment of integrated tax and claim`
  line `refund of the tax so paid ^3[in accordance with the provisions of section 54 of the Central Goods and`
  line `Services Tax Act or the rules made thereunder];`
  line
  line `(ii) a class of goods or services ^4[or both, on zero rated supply of which, the supplier may pay`
  line `integrated tax and claim the refund of tax so paid, in accordance with the provisions of section 54 of`
  line `the Central Goods and Services Tax Act or the rules made thereunder].]`
  line
  line `^5[(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (3) and (4), no refund of unutilised input`
  line `tax credit on account of zero rated supply of goods or of integrated tax paid on account of zero rated`
  line `supply of goods shall be allowed where such zero rated supply of goods are subjected to export duty.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 123 (w.e.f. 01-10-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 123, ibid. for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 01-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 153 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 153, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s. 153, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (5306)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Apportionment of tax and settlement of funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 2018, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5306&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Out of the integrated tax paid to the`
  line `Central Government,--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of inter-State supply of goods or services or both to an unregistered person or to a`
  line `registered person paying tax under section 10 of the Central Goods and Services Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of inter-State supply of goods or services or both where the registered person is not`
  line `eligible for input tax credit;`
  line
  line `(c) in respect of inter-State supply of goods or services or both made in a financial year to a`
  line `registered person, where he does not avail of the input tax credit within the specified period and thus`
  line `remains in the integrated tax account after expiry of the due date for furnishing of annual return for`
  line `such year in which the supply was made;`
  line
  line `(d) in respect of import of goods or services or both by an unregistered person or by a registered`
  line `person paying tax under section 10 of the Central Goods and Services Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(e) in respect of import of goods or services or both where the registered person is not eligible for`
  line `input tax credit;`
  line
  line `(f) in respect of import of goods or services or both made in a financial year by a registered`
  line `person, where he does not avail of the said credit within the specified period and thus remains in the`
  line `integrated tax account after expiry of the due date for furnishing of annual return for such year in`
  line `which the supply was received,`
  line
  line `the amount of tax calculated at the rate equivalent to the central tax on similar intra-State supply shall be`
  line `apportioned to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The balance amount of integrated tax remaining in the integrated tax account in respect of the`
  line `supply for which an apportionment to the Central Government has been done under sub-section (1) shall`
  line `be apportioned to the,--`
  line
  line `(a) State where such supply takes place; and`
  line
  line `(b) Central Government where such supply takes place in a Union territory:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the place of such supply made by any taxable person cannot be determined`
  line `separately, the said balance amount shall be apportioned to,--`
  line
  line `(a) each of the States; and`
  line
  line `(b) Central Government in relation to Union territories,`
  line
  line `in proportion to the total supplies made by such taxable person to each of such States or Union territories,`
  line `as the case may be, in a financial year:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the taxable person making such supplies is not identifiable, the said`
  line `balance amount shall be apportioned to all States and the Central Government in proportion to the amount`
  line `collected as State tax or, as the case may be, Union territory tax, by the respective State or, as the case`
  line `may be, by the Central Government during the immediately preceding financial year.`
  line
  line `^1[(2A) The amount not apportioned under sub-section (1) and sub-section (2) may, for the time being, on the recommendations of the Council, be apportioned at the rate of fifty per cent. to the Central Government and fifty per cent. to the State Governments or the Union territories, as the case may be, on ad hoc basis and shall be adjusted against the amount apportioned under the said sub-sections.]`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2) relating to apportionment of integrated tax shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to the apportionment of interest, penalty and compounding amount realised in connection`
  line `with the tax so apportioned.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an amount has been apportioned to the Central Government or a State Government under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), the amount collected as integrated tax shall stand`
  line `reduced by an amount equal to the amount so apportioned and the Central Government shall transfer to`
  line `the central tax account or Union territory tax account, an amount equal to the respective amounts`
  line `apportioned to the Central Government and shall transfer to the State tax account of the respective States`
  line `an amount equal to the amount apportioned to that State, in such manner and within such time as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(5) Any integrated tax apportioned to a State or, as the case may be, to the Central Government on`
  line `account of a Union territory, if subsequently found to be refundable to any person and refunded to such`
  line `person, shall be reduced from the amount to be apportioned under this section, to such State, or Central`
  line `Government on account of such Union territory, in such manner and within such time as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (50220)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 20
  title `Transfer of certain amounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 114 (w.e.f. 01-01-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=50220&sectionno=17A&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[17A. Transfer of certain amounts.--Where any amount has been transferred from the electronic`
  line `cash ledger under this Act to the electronic cash ledger under the State Goods and Services Tax Act or the`
  line `Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act, the Government shall transfer to the State tax account or the`
  line `Union territory tax account, an amount equal to the amount transferred from the electronic cash ledger, in`
  line `such manner and within such time, as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (5307)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 21
  title `Transfer of input tax credit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5307&sectionno=18&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `On utilisation of credit of integrated tax availed under this Act for`
  line `payment of,--`
  line
  line `(a) central tax in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (5) of section 49 of the Central`
  line `Goods and Services Tax Act, the amount collected as integrated tax shall stand reduced by an amount`
  line `equal to the credit so utilised and the Central Government shall transfer an amount equal to the`
  line `amount so reduced from the integrated tax account to the central tax account in such manner and`
  line `within such time as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) Union territory tax in accordance with the provisions of section 9 of the Union Territory`
  line `Goods and Services Tax Act, the amount collected as integrated tax shall stand reduced by an amount`
  line `equal to the credit so utilised and the Central Government shall transfer an amount equal to the`
  line `amount so reduced from the integrated tax account to the Union territory tax account in such manner`
  line `and within such time as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(c) State tax in accordance with the provisions of the respective State Goods and Services Tax`
  line `Act, the amount collected as integrated tax shall stand reduced by an amount equal to the credit so`
  line `utilised and shall be apportioned to the appropriate State Government and the Central Government`
  line `shall transfer the amount so apportioned to the account of the appropriate State Government in such`
  line `manner and within such time as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this Chapter, “appropriate State” in relation to a taxable`
  line `person, means the State or Union territory where he is registered or is liable to be registered under the`
  line `provisions of the Central Goods and Services Tax Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (5308)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 22
  title `Tax wrongfully collected and paid to Central Government or State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5308&sectionno=19&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) A`
  line `registered person who has paid integrated tax on a supply considered by him to be an inter-State supply,`
  line `but which is subsequently held to be an intra-State supply, shall be granted refund of the amount of`
  line `integrated tax so paid in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A registered person who has paid central tax and State tax or Union territory tax, as the case may`
  line `be, on a transaction considered by him to be an intra-State supply, but which is subsequently held to be an`
  line `inter-State supply, shall not be required to pay any interest on the amount of integrated tax payable.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (5309)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 23
  title `Application of provisions of Central Goods and Services Tax Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 154, for proviso (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5309&sectionno=20&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions`
  line `of this Act and the rules made thereunder, the provisions of Central Goods and Services Tax Act relating`
  line `to, ---`
  line
  line `(i) scope of supply;`
  line
  line `(ii) composite supply and mixed supply;`
  line
  line `(iii) time and value of supply;`
  line
  line `(iv) input tax credit;`
  line
  line `(v) registration;`
  line
  line `(vi) tax invoice, credit and debit notes;`
  line
  line `(vii) accounts and records;`
  line
  line `(viii) returns, other than late fee;`
  line
  line `(ix) payment of tax;`
  line
  line `(x) tax deduction at source;`
  line
  line `(xi) collection of tax at source;`
  line
  line `(xii) assessment;`
  line
  line `(xiii) refunds;`
  line
  line `(xiv) audit;`
  line
  line `(xv) inspection, search, seizure and arrest;`
  line
  line `(xvi) demands and recovery;`
  line
  line `(xvii) liability to pay in certain cases;`
  line
  line `(xviii) advance ruling;`
  line
  line `(xix) appeals and revision;`
  line
  line `(xx) presumption as to documents;`
  line
  line `(xxi) offences and penalties;`
  line
  line `(xxii) job work;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) electronic commerce;`
  line
  line `(xxiv) transitional provisions; and`
  line
  line `(xxv) miscellaneous provisions including the provisions relating to the imposition of interest and`
  line penalty,
  line
  line `shall, mutatis mutandis, apply, so far as may be, in relation to integrated tax as they apply in relation to`
  line `central tax as if they are enacted under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of tax deducted at source, the deductor shall deduct tax at the rate of two per`
  line `cent. from the payment made or credited to the supplier:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of tax collected at source, the operator shall collect tax at such rate`
  line `not exceeding two per cent, as may be notified on the recommendations of the Council, of the net value of`
  line `taxable supplies:`
  line
  line `Provided also that for the purposes of this Act, the value of a supply shall include any taxes, duties,`
  line `cesses, fees and charges levied under any law for the time being in force other than this Act, and the`
  line `Goods and Services Tax (Compensation to States) Act, if charged separately by the supplier:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in cases where the penalty is leviable under the Central Goods and Services Tax`
  line `Act and the State Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act, the`
  line `penalty leviable under this Act shall be the sum total of the said penalties.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided also that a maximum amount of forty crore rupees shall be payable for each appeal to be`
  line `filed before the Appellate Authority or the Appellate Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (5310)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 24
  title `Import of services made on or after the appointed day.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5310&sectionno=21&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Import of services made on or after`
  line `the appointed day shall be liable to tax under the provisions of this Act regardless of whether the`
  line `transactions for such import of services had been initiated before the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the tax on such import of services had been paid in full under the existing law, no tax`
  line `shall be payable on such import under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the tax on such import of services had been paid in part under the existing law,`
  line `the balance amount of tax shall be payable on such import under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section, a transaction shall be deemed to have been initiated`
  line `before the appointed day if either the invoice relating to such supply or payment, either in full or in part,`
  line `has been received or made before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (5311)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5311&sectionno=22&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the Government may`
  line `make rules for all or any of the matters which by this Act are required to be, or may be, prescribed or in`
  line `respect of which provisions are to be or may be made by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make rules conferred by this section shall include the power to give retrospective`
  line `effect to the rules or any of them from a date not earlier than the date on which the provisions of this Act`
  line `come into force.`
  line
  line `(4) Any rules made under sub-section(1) may provide that a contravention thereof shall be liable to a`
  line `penalty not exceeding ten thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (5312)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5312&sectionno=23&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, by notification, make regulations consistent with`
  line `this Act and the rules made thereunder to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (5313)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 27
  title `Laying of rules, regulations and notifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5313&sectionno=24&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the Government, every`
  line `regulation made by the Board and every notification issued by the Government under this Act, shall be`
  line `laid, as soon as may be, after it is made or issued, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session,`
  line `for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or in the`
  line `notification, as the case may be, or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation or the notification should`
  line `not be made, the rule or regulation or notification, as the case may be, shall thereafter have effect only in`
  line `such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or`
  line `regulation or notification, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (5314)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 28
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 134, for “three years” (w.e.f. 30-6-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116&sectionId=5314&sectionno=25&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00043_201713_1517807328116
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to any provision of this Act,`
  line `the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by a general or a special order published in`
  line `the Official Gazette, make such provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act or the rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder, as may be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing the said`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of ^1[five years] from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
